<item>
            <title>[LU-18917] TCU: implement per-user subdirectories in trash can</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18917</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Implement per-user subdirectories in Trash Can to separate user files. The directory name should be the UID of the inode being deleted, not the UID of the &lt;b&gt;process&lt;/b&gt; doing the deletion. The per-user directory should have &lt;tt&gt;inode-&amp;gt;i_uid&lt;/tt&gt; = UID and mode 0700 so that it can only be accessed by the user. The GID and PROJID should be taken from the configured &lt;tt&gt;mdd.&lt;b&gt;.trash_can_gid&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;mdd.&lt;/b&gt;.trash_can_projid&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
